//http://stackoverflow.com/questions/33063073/postgresql-max-value-for-every-user

#input

| Usr   | Phone | Value |
|-----------------------|
| Peter | 012   | 1     |
| Peter | 456   | 2     |
| Peter | 123   | 3     |
| Paul  | 789   | 3     |
| Paul  | 789   | 7     |
| Paul  | 789   | 10    |

#output

|  c1   | c2  | c3 |
|------------------|
| Peter | 123 | 3  |
| Paul  | 789 | 7  |

#constraint
{
	"constants": ["8"],
	"aggregation_functions": ["max"]
}

#solution

```sql
SELECT
    T1.Usr,
    T0.Phone,
    T1.max_Value 
FROM
    input1 AS T0 
JOIN
    (
        SELECT
            Usr,
            max(Value) AS max_Value 
        FROM
            input1 
        WHERE
            Value < 8 
        GROUP BY
            Usr
    ) AS T1 
        ON T1.Usr = T0.Usr 
        AND T1.max_Value = T0.Value 
ORDER BY
    T1.Usr DESC
```

```sql
select t1.*
from your_table t1
join (
    select usr, max(value) as max_value
    from your_table
    where value < 8
    group by usr
) t2 on t1.usr = t2.usr and t1.value = t2.max_value
```
